{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b365d161-937b-4137-9925-913032468230","content":"CLR activation logs aren't the right tool here. They diagnose **runtime loading** issues (e.g., wrong CLR version selected, runtime not found), not application-level exceptions like `NullReferenceException`.\n\nA `NullReferenceException` means your code is dereferencing a null reference at runtime — that's an application bug, not an activation problem.\n\n**To diagnose this, I'd need:**\n- The **stack trace** from the exception\n- The **relevant source code** around the crash site\n- Or a **crash dump** to analyze\n\n**Better approaches:**\n1. Share the exception stack trace so I can pinpoint the null reference\n2. Enable first-chance exception debugging in your IDE\n3. Collect a crash dump (I can help with that using the `dump-collect` skill)\n\nWould you like help with any of these instead?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6e7aaf8e-f2de-4edb-9c75-9a4b08879d6e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking me to analyze CLR activation logs to diagnose a NullReferenceException. However, there are a few issues:\n\n1. CLR activation logs are about how the CLR runtime is loaded/activated (mscoree.dll shim behavior), not about application-level exceptions like NullReferenceException.\n2. The user hasn't provided any logs or code to analyze.\n3. There's a `clr-activation-debugging` skill available that could help with CLR activation issues.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The user says their app crashes with a NullReferenceException and wants me to analyze CLR activation logs. \n\nCLR activation logs won't actually help here since they only track runtime loading, not application exceptions. I should ask the user for their actual crash details, stack trace, or relevant code instead, since those would be much more useful for diagnosing a NullReferenceException.","outputTokens":575},"id":"beb8619f-b6cd-4d8d-ada9-974e907da113","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01: